This paper is about video super-resolution using deep learning methods, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel approach to reduce the computational complexity of 3D convolutions, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.MM), machine learning theory (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
